- Oh, yeah.

719
01:04:26,200 --> 01:04:31,558
Now let's find James, and teach
that simple bastard a lesson too.

720
01:04:40,400 --> 01:04:42,470
Hiya, kids. Are we having fun?

721
01:04:42,600 --> 01:04:45,114
- Ted, what's happening?
- Who the hell are you?

722
01:04:45,240 --> 01:04:47,913
Hey, shut up, you!

723
01:04:48,040 --> 01:04:50,031
What the hell is that?

724
01:04:50,160 --> 01:04:51,991
- lt's a Taser.
- A what?

725
01:04:52,120 --> 01:04:54,953
A Taser. 65,000 volts of electricity.

726
01:04:55,080 --> 01:04:59,915
lt completely incapacitates the victim
without killing him. l got it on sale.

727
01:05:00,040 --> 01:05:01,871
Let's move it. Let's go.

728
01:05:02,000 --> 01:05:03,956
Put your hands up.

729
01:05:06,280 --> 01:05:07,872
Ted, you should do something.

730
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:11,037
lf you come up with any ideas,
please let me know.

731
01:05:11,160 --> 01:05:13,390
We have the right to know
what's going on.

732
01:05:13,520 --> 01:05:17,274
Hey, put a cork in it, sister.
You have no more rights.

733
01:05:17,400 --> 01:05:20,039
And you, buying a goddamn laser gun.

734
01:05:20,160 --> 01:05:22,037
- Taser.
- Whatever.

735
01:05:22,160 --> 01:05:26,073
- You've always gotta be so different.
- l'm in no mood. Just lay off.

736
01:05:26,200 --> 01:05:29,590
- No, you gotta be creative.
- l said lay off.

737
01:05:29,720 --> 01:05:35,033
- When l say ''now'', start running.
- (men continue arguing)

738
01:05:35,160 --> 01:05:38,550
You're an amazing man.
You know shit about absolutely nothing.

739
01:05:38,680 --> 01:05:41,114
Now l've just heard everything.

740
01:05:41,240 --> 01:05:42,878
Hold it, honey.

741
01:05:43,000 --> 01:05:46,356
You listen to me, you ltalian
son of a bitch, and you listen good.

742
01:05:46,480 --> 01:05:49,870
The day you tell me l don't know shit
and l let you get away with it

743
01:05:50,000 --> 01:05:53,834
- is the day that that ocean freezes over.
- That's it. You're over.

744
01:05:57,160 --> 01:05:59,116
Now!

745
01:06:08,160 --> 01:06:11,709
- That's my car!
- Looks pretty undriveable. Come on!

746
01:06:16,840 --> 01:06:19,274
Come on, let's go!

747
01:06:22,240 --> 01:06:23,992
Ted!

748
01:06:24,840 --> 01:06:29,072
- Ted, what the hell's going on?
- l left out a couple of things about myself.

749
01:06:29,200 --> 01:06:32,954
- l'm waiting, you son of a bitch.
- First, my name isn't Ted. lt's Carl.

750
01:06:33,080 --> 01:06:35,640
From now on when you yell for me
in a panic, yell Carl.

751
01:06:35,760 --> 01:06:37,318
There's more?

752
01:06:37,440 --> 01:06:40,637
Last night you and Jack Berger
had a fight in your apartment.

753
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:43,991
How the hell could you
have possibly known that?

754
01:06:45,040 --> 01:06:47,759
Look, Susan, l don't live in your building.

755
01:06:47,880 --> 01:06:51,350
l am a garbageman.
l live across the street from you.

756
01:06:51,480 --> 01:06:53,994
l have been watching you
every day for six weeks.

757
01:06:54,120 --> 01:06:57,476
Wait a minute! Wait a minute.
You have been spying on me?

758
01:06:57,600 --> 01:07:00,717
- l don't really consider it spying.
- What do you consider it?

759
01:07:00,840 --> 01:07:03,877
Let me finish! You and Jack
had a fight, you left angry.

760
01:07:04,000 --> 01:07:06,639
The next morning
l found Berger's body in the trash.

761
01:07:06,760 --> 01:07:09,069
- Jack's body?
- Somebody killed him, Susan.

762
01:07:09,200 --> 01:07:11,714
- For a while l thought it was you.
- Jack is not dead.

763
01:07:11,840 --> 01:07:15,594
- Jack was at my apartment last night.
- Trust me, Jack is dead.

764
01:07:15,720 --> 01:07:18,632
Jack came over because
there was some mix-up with a tape

765
01:07:18,760 --> 01:07:22,719
and l went down to my car to get
the right tape and... The tape, the tape.

766
01:07:22,840 --> 01:07:26,628
This is what had Jack so worked up.
We gotta get this to the police.

767
01:07:26,760 --> 01:07:30,116
- What the hell was that for?
- For lying to me. l hate liars!

768
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:33,353
Hates liars?

769
01:07:35,800 --> 01:07:38,155
That's for spying on me!

770
01:07:41,040 --> 01:07:42,393
Come on!

771
01:07:49,160 --> 01:07:51,116
(groans)

772
01:07:53,280 --> 01:07:54,998
What happened?

773
01:07:55,120 --> 01:07:58,271
lt was something.
You got struck by lightning.

774
01:07:59,800 --> 01:08:02,712
- Really?
- A freak storm.

775
01:08:10,360 --> 01:08:12,316
- Police!
- Thank God.

776
01:08:19,520 --> 01:08:21,670
- Police!
- Hello!

777
01:08:21,800 --> 01:08:23,756
Over here, by the playground.

778
01:08:35,760 --> 01:08:36,636
Ew.

779
01:08:47,640 --> 01:08:49,073
Sorry, guys.

780
01:08:49,200 --> 01:08:53,716
Wait! lt's not what it looks like.
Please, give us a hand.

781
01:08:53,840 --> 01:08:56,638
No, l'm really not into it, but thanks.

782
01:08:56,760 --> 01:09:01,515
Carl! Come on, Carl. Everything
l ever said about you, just kidding.

783
01:09:01,640 --> 01:09:03,596
He was.

784
01:09:04,960 --> 01:09:09,636
You're not really gonna leave us here,
are you? That would be...

785
01:09:19,000 --> 01:09:22,549
- Come on, come on, already!
- About a thousand keys here.

786
01:09:25,960 --> 01:09:28,076
- Try this one.
- l'm trying.

787
01:09:36,000 --> 01:09:37,274
Hey, hey, hey!

788
01:09:39,400 --> 01:09:41,277
- l got it!
- (Biff) Look out.

789
01:09:48,640 --> 01:09:50,596
lt's my turn, asshole!

790
01:09:51,760 --> 01:09:53,557
- What is he doing?
- What are you doing?

791
01:09:53,680 --> 01:09:55,398
- l'm crashing!
- Down!

792
01:10:13,600 --> 01:10:15,556
l'm back.

793
01:10:16,160 --> 01:10:18,116
Let's go, honey.

794
01:10:20,800 --> 01:10:23,837
Chief, we got 'em. We found 'em.

795
01:10:30,040 --> 01:10:34,318
Allow me to introduce myself.
l'm Maxwell Potterdam the third.

796
01:10:34,440 --> 01:10:37,876
Maybe you've heard of me. California
magazine just did a piece on me.

797
01:10:38,000 --> 01:10:41,037
With the exception of being
misquoted several times,

798
01:10:41,160 --> 01:10:44,277
l thought it was a pretty good article.

799
01:10:44,400 --> 01:10:48,757
Anyway, all that is... unimportant.

800
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:54,071
This... is what's important.

801
01:10:54,200 --> 01:10:56,919
Let's put these folks in the car

802
01:10:57,040 --> 01:11:00,589
and go someplace a little more noisy.

803
01:11:02,960 --> 01:11:04,916
Come on, move it.

804
01:11:09,960 --> 01:11:11,632
Hey.

805
01:11:11,760 --> 01:11:14,399
That's them. Getting into that limo.

806
01:11:16,840 --> 01:11:20,833
- What the hell's goin' on?
- l don't know, but we're gonna find out.

807
01:11:50,920 --> 01:11:53,275
l knew this was gonna get heavy.

808
01:11:58,440 --> 01:12:01,193
A lot of good this thing is gonna do us.

809
01:12:02,720 --> 01:12:07,999
A pellet gun? You've been holding me
hostage all night with an air rifle?

810
01:12:08,120 --> 01:12:10,509
- Shut up.
- This is too much.

811
01:12:11,200 --> 01:12:13,555
We gotta find a way in there.

812
01:12:15,040 --> 01:12:17,429
l... l got a plan.

813
01:12:25,200 --> 01:12:27,031
That oughta do them.

814
01:12:27,160 --> 01:12:30,709
l would love to see
those bastards try and top this.

815
01:12:30,840 --> 01:12:36,039
l would pay a million pesos to see their
faces when they try to stop this baby.

816
01:12:36,160 --> 01:12:39,596
Hey, pal, the next time
we see Carl and James,

817
01:12:39,720 --> 01:12:43,269
it's gonna be Walt
handing them their walking papers.

818
01:12:43,400 --> 01:12:45,755
(clinking)

819
01:12:45,880 --> 01:12:48,838
(whispers) Somebody's coming.

820
01:12:48,960 --> 01:12:50,154
(mouths)

821
01:12:50,880 --> 01:12:52,836
(James) Come on!

822
01:12:54,320 --> 01:12:57,392
- Come on, move it. Get up there.
- (pizza man) OK, l'm going.

823
01:13:25,680 --> 01:13:28,592
We do live in extraordinary times.

824
01:13:28,720 --> 01:13:31,792
The lengths one has to go
to get the job done.

825
01:13:31,920 --> 01:13:35,356
You're destroying the environment
and you don't even care.

826
01:13:35,480 --> 01:13:38,870
How do you do it?
How do you live with yourself?

827
01:13:39,000 --> 01:13:40,956
Gentlemen.

828
01:13:42,000 --> 01:13:44,309
Although l'd prefer to dump you

829
01:13:44,440 --> 01:13:47,910
along with the rest of this waste
at the bottom of the Pacific,

830
01:13:48,040 --> 01:13:52,238
recent disruptions in our operation
have created a problem,

831
01:13:52,360 --> 01:13:57,912
and now the Las Playas landfill
will become your final resting place.

832
01:13:58,040 --> 01:14:00,634
- Buried alive?
- Not to worry.

833
01:14:00,760 --> 01:14:04,878
You'll probably run out of oxygen
before we reach the dump site.

834
01:14:06,760 --> 01:14:08,478
Seal 'em up.

835
01:14:08,600 --> 01:14:10,272
(Susan) No!

836
01:14:10,400 --> 01:14:12,675
(muffled shouting)

837
01:14:20,760 --> 01:14:23,115
Hold on, everyone!

838
01:14:28,800 --> 01:14:29,755
Hey!

839
01:14:33,960 --> 01:14:36,394
Something's wrong. We're not stopping.

840
01:14:36,520 --> 01:14:38,875
- What?
- We're not stopping!

841
01:14:39,960 --> 01:14:42,428
Aaargh!

842
01:14:48,280 --> 01:14:51,238
- What the hell was that?
- Move your ass and find out.

843
01:14:51,360 --> 01:14:55,069
No, you two stay.
l want those barrels sealed. You two.

844
01:15:03,520 --> 01:15:05,988
- Everybody all right?
- (Louis) Yeah.

845
01:15:06,120 --> 01:15:08,076
Oh, shit.

846
01:15:10,480 --> 01:15:12,516
Get off of me.

847
01:15:40,960 --> 01:15:42,916
Come on, let's go.

848
01:15:43,040 --> 01:15:46,077
No, no, no. No, no, no.

849
01:15:46,200 --> 01:15:51,320
l am not some kind of comic-book
superhero. l'm a pizza man.

850
01:15:52,000 --> 01:15:54,958
- Stay here and keep an eye on him.
- Yeah, right.

851
01:16:16,480 --> 01:16:18,675
l want the trucks moving immediately.

852
01:16:18,800 --> 01:16:22,349
l want every goddamn drop of waste
dumped before the sun rises.

853
01:16:22,480 --> 01:16:24,436
OK, Mr Potterdam.

854
01:16:34,840 --> 01:16:37,798
(muffled shouting)

855
01:17:16,720 --> 01:17:19,188
Go this way!

856
01:17:25,200 --> 01:17:26,519
Jesus!

857
01:17:28,720 --> 01:17:29,914
Holy shit!

858
01:17:48,480 --> 01:17:51,472
(driver) All right,
l'll pick it up on my way back.

859
01:17:54,560 --> 01:17:57,836
- Hi, Carl.
- Hi, James. How are you?

860
01:17:58,640 --> 01:18:00,596
Never better.

861
01:18:01,800 --> 01:18:03,756
Susan! Come on.

862
01:18:18,720 --> 01:18:20,870
(Carl) Come on! We can't lose 'em!

863
01:18:23,640 --> 01:18:26,757
- (James) We're not gonna make it.
- We'll make it.

864
01:18:32,560 --> 01:18:34,516
(police siren)

865
01:18:40,320 --> 01:18:42,276
South Bay Security. Freeze!

866
01:18:50,560 --> 01:18:54,269
Rent-a-cops. l hate rent-a-cops too.

867
01:19:06,240 --> 01:19:09,357
Carl! What the hell are we doing?

868
01:19:09,480 --> 01:19:11,596
l think l love this girl.

869
01:19:11,720 --> 01:19:13,995
Really? How do you know?

870
01:19:14,120 --> 01:19:16,873
She let me feel the bumps on her head.

871
01:19:17,000 --> 01:19:18,956
(both) Whoa!

872
01:19:20,160 --> 01:19:23,835
- (Carl) lt looks like the bolt broke!
- No shit!

873
01:19:29,360 --> 01:19:31,590
- Hang on.
- OK.

874
01:19:34,040 --> 01:19:36,031
Trees! Trees!

875
01:19:37,520 --> 01:19:39,431
- Carl!
- What?

876
01:19:39,560 --> 01:19:42,199
- How you doin' over there?
- Piece of cake.

877
01:19:51,840 --> 01:19:53,796
- You need help.
- (growls)

878
01:20:09,120 --> 01:20:10,075
Carl!

879
01:20:16,400 --> 01:20:18,356
James!

880
01:20:19,960 --> 01:20:22,235
Hey, Carl!

881
01:20:22,360 --> 01:20:24,396
l think l got a problem over here.

882
01:20:24,520 --> 01:20:27,557
All right, let me think of something.

883
01:20:30,240 --> 01:20:34,074
Hey, James, l didn't think of anything yet.

884
01:20:39,040 --> 01:20:43,192
Hey, Carl! l definitely
got a problem over here!

885
01:20:45,400 --> 01:20:47,516
l'm coming.

886
01:20:55,360 --> 01:20:57,316
(crash)

887
01:21:36,000 --> 01:21:37,956
Mr Potterdam?

888
01:22:07,480 --> 01:22:10,233
We're lookin' pretty outnumbered here.

889
01:22:12,280 --> 01:22:14,840
l got an idea. Follow me.

890
01:22:29,080 --> 01:22:32,834
- What the hell are you doing?
- Protecting the environment.

891
01:22:39,000 --> 01:22:40,956
- Freeze.
- What are you...

892
01:22:46,600 --> 01:22:48,670
Everybody freeze or l blow his head off!

893
01:22:48,800 --> 01:22:50,472
- He'll do it.
- l'm not kiddin'.

894
01:22:50,600 --> 01:22:52,158
- Don't push him.
- l mean it.

895
01:22:52,280 --> 01:22:53,349
His whole head.

896
01:22:53,480 --> 01:22:56,392
You two with the weapons,
over the side. Do it now!

897
01:23:05,160 --> 01:23:07,390
Yeah, man, l know you.

898
01:23:07,520 --> 01:23:11,991
l know what you're thinking. ''We got us
another crazy white boy with a gun.''

899
01:23:12,120 --> 01:23:16,750
Well, let me tell you, human life means
very little to me at this point in time.

900
01:23:16,880 --> 01:23:19,519
(police siren)

901
01:23:26,320 --> 01:23:28,880
Relax, James, the cops are here.

902
01:23:29,000 --> 01:23:33,516
This is the police.
You all drop those weapons.

903
01:23:36,440 --> 01:23:39,398
Yeah. Yeah, you!
You there with the pellet gun,

904
01:23:39,520 --> 01:23:43,149
drop it or l'll blow
your butt away for sure, buddy.

905
01:23:43,280 --> 01:23:46,113
(garbled arguing)

906
01:23:51,160 --> 01:23:56,951
A pellet gun? Do you think we'd use
a pellet gun for something like this?

907
01:23:57,080 --> 01:23:58,991
Get 'em!

908
01:24:05,520 --> 01:24:07,511
l gotta find Susan.

909
01:24:13,200 --> 01:24:14,952
Susan!

910
01:24:15,760 --> 01:24:17,512
Susan!

911
01:24:29,800 --> 01:24:31,313
Uh-oh.

912
01:24:31,880 --> 01:24:33,791
Stop 'em before they get away!

913
01:24:35,880 --> 01:24:38,713
Susan! Susan!

914
01:24:40,880 --> 01:24:42,836
Susan!

915
01:25:20,920 --> 01:25:23,115
(Susan) Help!

916
01:25:23,960 --> 01:25:25,837
Susan.

917
01:25:29,840 --> 01:25:32,195
Ow! Oh!

918
01:25:43,800 --> 01:25:46,155
- Where are we?
- You don't wanna know.

919
01:26:14,080 --> 01:26:16,833
(James) Carl! Carl, over here! Get down!

920
01:26:29,840 --> 01:26:31,478
Come on. Move out.

921
01:26:33,560 --> 01:26:35,516
Move! Everybody in the car.

922
01:26:41,320 --> 01:26:43,276
(Susan) Get the door open.

923
01:26:44,680 --> 01:26:47,194
- Start the car.
- (Louis) lt won't start.

924
01:26:49,040 --> 01:26:52,157
- Get out of the car!
- Oh, shit!

925
01:27:40,200 --> 01:27:42,156
(doll) Ouch/ Be careful/

926
01:28:10,640 --> 01:28:12,596
High five!

927
01:28:18,880 --> 01:28:20,836
Your car, sir.

928
01:28:43,920 --> 01:28:45,751
Smile, butthead.

929
01:29:01,080 --> 01:29:02,832
Whoa.

930
01:29:13,840 --> 01:29:15,796
(laughing)

931
01:29:33,480 --> 01:29:37,439
( ''Give a Little Love'' by Ziggy Marley
and the Melody Makers)

932
01:29:57,440 --> 01:29:59,795
Hey, it's not what it looks like.

933
01:30:00,840 --> 01:30:03,195
We're respectable peace officers.

934
01:30:04,000 --> 01:30:07,390
lt's just all one big, funny mix-up.

935
01:30:07,520 --> 01:30:09,476
(barks)

936
01:30:17,160 --> 01:30:18,912
No!

937
01:30:23,240 --> 01:30:25,470
Shoo! Shoo!

938
01:30:25,600 --> 01:30:26,999
Get outta here!

939
01:30:27,120 --> 01:30:30,112
Good morning/ You're listening
to the Poorman on open-line.

940
01:30:30,240 --> 01:30:34,995
We're gonna take our next caller.
Hello/ You're on open-line. Go ahead.

941
01:30:35,120 --> 01:30:37,236
Yeah, hi. My name's Stacey.

942
01:30:37,360 --> 01:30:40,670
l have a boyfriend who l've been
going out with for two years now.

943
01:30:40,800 --> 01:30:43,633
He works nights
as a delivery boy for a pizza place.

944
01:30:43,760 --> 01:30:45,830
Last night he never came home

945
01:30:45,960 --> 01:30:48,758
and l am positive he is out
sleeping with another girl.

946
01:30:48,880 --> 01:30:52,634
(Poorman) Well, l think you should
definitely dump the dude/

947
01:34:12,840 --> 01:34:16,310
Visiontext Subtitles: Sally Lewis

948
01:34:24,280 --> 01:34:26,236
ENHOH

